    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="651"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5747/35.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Panama</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Panama</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I am instructed by my Government to
                    propose to your excellency’s Government Mr. Edwin Denby as umpire of the mixed
                    commission mentioned in Articles VI and XV of the convention of November 18,
                    1903, which I do with great pleasure and the hope that Mr. Denby will be
                    acceptable to your excellency’s Government.</p>
                <p>I renew, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. A. Arango.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
